RACE.FOOTNOTES: G G RULES saved ground while being forwardly placed, slipped through during the drive and was up in the final sixteenth to win going away. CHEATER'S WALTZ saved ground setting the pace, drifted out slightly leaving the quarter pole and then held on fairly well during the drive to end up on even terms with Bossy Pegasus. BOSSY PEGASUS was reserved off the early pace, came three-wide into the stretch, angled in during the drive and finished in a late rally to end up in a dead-heat with Cheater's Waltz for the show. FLORA saved ground while being unhurried but lacked a rally when asked. NOMI LACKEE prompted the early pace while racing two-wide and weakened. ZARAGOZA bumped at the start with Ted's Candy Girl and failed to menace thereafter.
